An Australian couple have made a desperate plea for help after they became stranded in Thailand with their newborn twins, born via a Thai surrogate mother.

Kate and Adam Osborne, from Kempsey, on the mid north coast of New South Wales, are one of the many Australian couples who have become locked in legal battles after changes to Thailand's commercial surrogacy laws.

They reportedly turned to Thai surrogacy as a last resort after numerous failed IVF attempts in Australia.

'They are in a tiny motel room with two newborns and money is running out fast,' their friend Jen Farrell wrote on a fundraising page set up to help the family.

